A group of around 40 AI researchersrepresenting labs like OpenAI, Google DeepMind, Meta, and Anthropichave issued warnings that internal complexity in modern AI models is outpacing our ability to understand them citeturn0search0turn0search2.

2. What specifically are they worried about?

  • Chain of Thought (CoT) reasoning: This internal step-by-step AI reasoning may not always be visible or interpretable by humans.
  • Advanced models, especially those using multi-agent debate or extended reasoning, are becoming opaqueeven to the engineers who build them citeturn0news24turn0search9.

Implications for AI trust and safety

  1. Transparency gaps
    As models grow more complex, it becomes harder to audit how decisions are madeeven for developers.

  2. Limitations of chainofthought monitoring
